b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":1866,"category_name":"News","pr_category_id":"1","title_name":"Regarding an Issue That May Prevent iOS Players From Purchasing Items Under Certain Conditions","message":"<div>We have confirmed an issue that prevents some players from purchasing content in the Shop under certain conditions after updating to Version 2.3.0. Please see the following for further details.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Affected Players<\/div><div>Players using iOS devices<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Issue Details<\/div><div>If a player&#39;s device is configured as described below, the prices of certain items in the Shop will be displayed as &quot;error,&quot; preventing players from purchasing the affected item.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Issue Cause<\/div><div>This issue will occur if the In-App Purchases option under iTunes &amp; App Store Purchases under Content &amp; Privacy Restrictions in the Screen Time section of the device&#39;s Settings is set to &quot;Don&#39;t Allow,&quot; or if the In-App Purchases toggle under the Restrictions section of the device&#39;s Settings is disabled. (Please note that the names of options and their location in the device&#39;s Settings depends on the version of iOS that is installed on the device.)<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>If you encounter this issue, please verify that the cause is as described above. We apologize for any inconvenience that this issue may cause.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div>","start_time":1608609600,"prev_article_id":"1864","next_article_id":"1823","image_path":"","update_time":1608600649}}}'